claim.claim-text:
1. A computer-implemented method of providing caller identification (ID) information to a mobile device, comprising
receiving caller ID information from local address books of a plurality of mobile devices used by a plurality of different users;
generating a pooled address book that aggregates the caller ID information received from the plurality of mobile devices;
receiving a request from a first mobile device used by a first user for caller ID information associated with a telephone number of a second mobile device used by a second user, the caller ID information associated with the telephone number not present in a local address book of the first mobile device;
identifying the caller ID information associated with the telephone number in the pooled address book, the identified caller ID information received from a local address book of a third mobile device used by a third user; and
sending the identified caller ID information associated with the telephone number to the first mobile device.

8. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium encoded with executable computer program code for providing caller identification (ID) information to a mobile device, the computer program code comprising program code for:
receiving caller ID information from local address books of a plurality of mobile devices used by a plurality of different users;
generating a pooled address book that aggregates the caller ID information received from the plurality of mobile devices;
receiving a request from a first mobile device used by a first user for caller ID information associated with a telephone number of a second mobile device used by a second user, the caller ID information associated with the telephone number not present in a local address book of the first mobile device;
identifying the caller ID information in the pooled address book associated with the telephone number in the pooled address book, the identified caller ID information received from a local address book of a third mobile device used by a third user; and
sending the identified caller ID information associated with the telephone number to the first mobile device.

15. A computer for providing caller identification (ID) information to a mobile device, comprising:
a non-transitory computer-readable storage medium storing executable computer program instructions comprising instructions for:
receiving caller ID information from local address books of a plurality of mobile devices used by a plurality of different users;
generating a pooled address book that aggregates the caller ID information received from the plurality of mobile devices;
receiving a request from a first mobile device used by a first user for caller ID information associated with a telephone number of a second mobile device used by a second user, the caller ID information associated with the telephone number not present in a local address book of the first mobile device;
identifying the caller ID information associated with the telephone number in the pooled address book, the identified caller ID information received from a local address book of a third mobile device used by a third user; and

sending the identified caller ID information associated with the telephone number to the first mobile device.

22. A computer-implemented method of obtaining caller identification (ID) information associated with a telephone number, comprising:
sending caller ID information from a local address book of a first mobile device used by a first user to a caller information server, the caller information server adapted to generate a pooled address book that aggregates caller ID information received from local address books of a plurality of mobile devices used by a plurality of different users;
detecting an incoming communication received by the first mobile device from a telephone number of a second mobile device used by a second user;
responsive to the telephone number not being stored in the local address book of the first mobile device, sending a request to the caller information server requesting caller ID information for the telephone number, wherein the caller information server is adapted to identify caller ID information for the telephone number in the pooled address book, the identified caller ID information received from a local address book of a third mobile device used by a third user; and
receiving, from the caller information server, the caller ID information for the telephone number.
